title: Israel Heads to Its Fifth Election in Four Years
description:
A.M. Edition for Oct. 31. Veteran Israeli politician Benjamin Netanyahu could be on the verge of a political comeback as voters head to the polls on Tuesday. WSJ correspondent Dov Lieber says that after repeated elections, there are few issues left to be debated, leaving voter turnout as the main thrust of the campaign. Luke Vargas hosts.
